<subSubSection pageNumber="742" type="discussion">
<paragraph pageNumber="742">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="742">Note:</emphasis>
Heine (in 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Aubréville">Aubreville</normalizedToken>
&amp; Leroy, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="742">
Fl. 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Nouvelle-Calédonie">Nouvelle-Caledonie</normalizedToken>
</emphasis>
7: 132. 1975) wrongly indicated Hermann material (BM) as 
<typeStatus>lectotype</typeStatus>
but, in the absence of a reference in the protologue to 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Linnaeus’">Linnaeus'</normalizedToken>
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="742">
<volumeTitle>Flora Zeylanica</volumeTitle>
</emphasis>
, this cannot be original material for this name. Heine took up 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Physalis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="minima">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="742">P. minima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the sense of 
<taxonomicName authority="Roem. &amp; Schult" authorityName="Roem. &amp; Schult" authorityYear="1819" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Physalis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lagascae">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="742">P. lagascae</emphasis>
Roem. &amp; Schult
</taxonomicName>
, and was followed by a number of later authors. However, others have treated it as a synonym of 
<taxonomicName authority="L." authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Physalis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="angulata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="742">P. angulata</emphasis>
L.
</taxonomicName>
(see Nicolson &amp; al. in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="742">Regnum Veg</emphasis>
119: 248. 1988), and this is confirmed by 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Edmonds’">Edmonds'</normalizedToken>
formal typification.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
